data.description: Welcome to Loma’s premier oasis, home and property.  Conveniently located just 1 mile north of I-70 off 13 Road, this property has everything you could want in a home.  Glorious sunrises and sunsets, unobstructed views of the Colorado Monument, 1.65 acres of grasslands - WITH water shares!  Three animal corrals, 9 outbuildings total with ample space and opportunity for you to enjoy this property for years to come. The main house is an open layout with 3 bedrooms and 1 bath with mature landscaping and ample opportunities for you to customize your living space in any manner you see fit.   You will fall in love with the inviting layout of this small but cozy home.   Excellent insulation holds warm, gas fireplace heat in the winter and stays cool all summer long thanks in part to the like new swamp cooler and mature trees surrounding the property that shades and keeps you cool on those hot summer days.    Along with the best views in the valley, this property hosts some of the most amazing star gazing/meteor showers one will find in all of Colorado, not to mention rotating seasonal landscaping that starts in the early spring and lasts all the way through October.  Enjoy the sounds of migrating sand cranes, geese, and multiple families of hummingbirds that return each year to nest in the trees and bushes that surround this location. The croaking frogs, crickets and other wildlife will make you wonder why you didn’t leave the city life sooner. With a two-car garage, work shop space, corrals for animals and plenty of covered buildings for all your outdoor toys, this place is ready for you to put your own signature stamp on its unique spaces. Not to mention RV hookups in the back driveway for you or your friends to enjoy all that Loma life has to offer. It has sturdy bones and endless possibilities and is ready for the next adventures, love and laughter to come. It truly is country living with the convenience of being just 5 miles away from the wonderful community and schools of Fruita, and 1 mile away from the Kokopelli Bike trailhead and Loma Boat Launch on the Colorado River.   Your next home awaits you in Loma, Colorado and I can’t wait for you to see this place in person to truly justify all of the opportunities that this unique property provides. Enjoy 1303 13 Road’s endless sunsets, sitting by the campfire, stargazing and having real space to call your own little slice of heaven in Western Colorado.
